#### Install
```bash
$ [sudo] pip install google-chrome-cli
```

#### CLI
```bash
usage: google-chrome command [args]

Available commands:
    open                    open urls
    refresh                 refresh active tab or tabs by url
    close                   close tab

    url                     active tab url
    urls                    list of urls

    fullscreen-detect       return true/false if fullscreen active
    fullscreen-enter        enter fullscreen
    fullscreen-exit         exit fullscreen

    audio                   list tabs with active audio

    kill                    kill Chrome Google.app process
    pid                     Chrome Google.app pid

run `google-chrome COMMAND --help` for more infos
```

#### Examples
```bash
$ google-chrome open "https://github.com/" "https://google.com/"
```
```bash
$ google-chrome refresh "https://github.com/"
```
```bash
$ google-chrome urls
https://github.com/
https://google.com/
```

detect tabs with playing audio
```bash
$ google-chrome audio
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XXX
```

